        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Broader connections"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "n0oms07wfsn",
          "class": null,
          "textAlign": null,
          "rtl": null,
          "suggestionId": null,
          "suggestionTimestamp": null,
          "suggestionUserId": null,
          "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
          "suggestionKind": null,
          "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In addition to these links between developmental psychology, cognitive neuroscience, computational models, and linguistics, statistical learning research connects with several additional fields. One of these is communication disorders. Challenges in statistical learning have been observed in individuals with a range of developmental disabilities, particularly those that involve language, such as developmental language disorder (e.g., "
          },
          {
            "type": "citation",
            "attrs": {
              "id": "n0mxsbnc9vb",
              "href": null,
              "value": "",
              "unstructuredValue": "<p id=\"nohvzcifssf\" data-reactroot=\"\">Lammertink, I., Boersma, P., Wijnen, F., &amp; Rispens, J. (2017). Statistical learning in specific language impairment: A meta-analysis. <em>Journal of Speech, Language, and Hearing Research: JSLHR,</em> <em>60</em>(12), 3474\u20133486.</p>",
              "customLabel": "Lammertink et al., 2017",
              "suggestionId": null,
              "suggestionTimestamp": null,
              "suggestionUserId": null,
              "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
              "suggestionKind": null,
              "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") and dyslexia (e.g., "
          },
          {
            "type": "citation",
            "attrs": {
              "id": "nw16js5mlle",
              "href": null,
              "value": "",
              "unstructuredValue": "<p id=\"nyylrmc1mgq\" data-reactroot=\"\">Lee, S. M. K., Cui, Y., &amp; Tong, S. X. (2022). Toward a model of statistical learning and reading: Evidence from a meta-analysis. <em>Review of Educational Research,</em> <em>92</em>(4), 651\u2013691.</p>",
              "customLabel": "Lee, Cui, & Tong, 2022",
              "suggestionId": null,
              "suggestionTimestamp": null,
              "suggestionUserId": null,
              "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
              "suggestionKind": null,
              "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "). These issues dovetail with broader questions about individual differences in statistical learning and how they may relate to language skills in the population more generally (e.g., "
          },
          {
            "type": "citation",
            "attrs": {
              "id": "nt2af45g215",
              "href": null,
              "value": "",
              "unstructuredValue": "<p id=\"n5m94p1zr4u\" data-reactroot=\"\">Bogaerts, L., Siegelman, N., &amp; Frost, R. (2021). Statistical learning and language impairments: Toward more precise theoretical accounts. <em>Perspectives on Psychological Science,</em> <em>16</em>(2), 319\u2013337.</p>",
              "customLabel": "Bogaerts, Siegelman, & Frost, 2021",
              "suggestionId": null,
              "suggestionTimestamp": null,
              "suggestionUserId": null,
              "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
              "suggestionKind": null,
              "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ")."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "attrs": {
          "id": "nfhwslcrx4f",
          "class": null,
          "textAlign": null,
          "rtl": null,
          "suggestionId": null,
          "suggestionTimestamp": null,
          "suggestionUserId": null,
          "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
          "suggestionKind": null,
          "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Another field with intriguing connections to statistical learning is comparative psychology. Statistical learning research with nonhuman animals has demonstrated both similarities and dissimilarities with human learners (for review, see "
          },
          {
            "type": "citation",
            "attrs": {
              "id": "nhaohzo2eec",
              "href": null,
              "value": "",
              "unstructuredValue": "<p id=\"n90ah7r1x58\" data-reactroot=\"\">Santolin, C., &amp; Saffran, J. R. (2018). Constraints on statistical learning across species. <em>Trends in Cognitive Sciences,</em> <em>22</em>(1), 52\u201363.</p>",
              "customLabel": "Santolin & Saffran, 2018",
              "suggestionId": null,
              "suggestionTimestamp": null,
              "suggestionUserId": null,
              "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
              "suggestionKind": null,
              "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "; "
          },
          {
            "type": "citation",
            "attrs": {
              "id": "n3qhp5l7eaj",
              "href": null,
              "value": "",
              "unstructuredValue": "<p id=\"n5ck70rrboh\" data-reactroot=\"\">Wilson, B., Spierings, M., Ravignani, A., Mueller, J. L., Mintz, T. H., Wijnen, F., van der Kant, A., Smith, K., &amp; Rey, A. (2020). Non\u2010adjacent dependency learning in humans and other animals. <em>Topics in Cognitive Science,</em> <em>12</em>(3), 843\u2013858.</p>",
              "customLabel": "Wilson et al., 2020",
              "suggestionId": null,
              "suggestionTimestamp": null,
              "suggestionUserId": null,
              "suggestionDiscussionId": null,
              "suggestionKind": null,
              "suggestionOriginalAttrs": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "). Better understanding of these confluences and divergences may help us to gain traction on key questions concerning human evolution."
          }
        ]
      },
